# Exploration: cat

## Test scope
  135 behavioral groups: 73 unique, 62 shared

  Contexts referenced below:
    formatted_minimal:
      write "input.txt" "first line\nsecond line with trailing spaces\n	indented w..."
      write "other.txt" "hello world"
    words_minimal:
      write "input.txt" "aardvark\nabbreviation\nabout\nabstract\naccept\naccepted..."
      write "other.txt" "hello world"

## Observed: 10/10 flags
  10 uniquely observable, 0 distinguishable via flag pairs
  robustness: 10 verified in all contexts, 0 in most, 0 context-dependent

Aliases: -A = --show-all, -E = --show-ends, -T = --show-tabs, -b = --number-nonblank, -n = --number, -s = --squeeze-blank, -v = --show-nonprinting

## Verified behavior (flag produced observable output)
  -A  # equivalent to -vET
    tested: "-A" "input.txt" "other.txt" in formatted_minimal
    | flag adds 28 lines: first line$, second line with trailing spaces$, ^Iindented with tab$,     indented with spaces$, ^I ^Imixed tabs and spaces$
    | flag removes 28 lines: first line, second line with trailing spaces, 	indented with tab,     indented with spaces, 	 	mixed tabs and spaces
    without flag:
      first line
      second line with trailing spaces
      	indented with tab
          indented with spaces
      	 	mixed tabs and spaces
      
            ... (22 more)
    with flag:
      first line$
      second line with trailing spaces$
      ^Iindented with tab$
          indented with spaces$
      ^I ^Imixed tabs and spaces$
      $
            ... (22 more)
  -E  # display $ at end of each line
    tested: "-E" "input.txt" "other.txt" in words_minimal
    | flag adds 1513 lines: aardvark$, abbreviation$, about$, abstract$, accept$
    | flag removes 1513 lines: aardvark, abbreviation, about, abstract, accept
    without flag:
      aardvark
      abbreviation
      about
      abstract
      accept
      accepted
            ... (1507 more)
    with flag:
      aardvark$
      abbreviation$
      about$
      abstract$
      accept$
      accepted$
            ... (1507 more)
  -T  # display TAB characters as ^I
